GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 2
HOUSE BILL 1035
Committee Substitute Favorable 5/5/26
Short Title: Even-Yr Elections/Pink Hill. (Local)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
April 23, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE THAT MUNICIPAL ELECTIONS IN THE TOWN OF PINK HILL
3 BE CONDUCTED IN EVEN-NUMBERED YEARS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. Section 3.1 of the Charter of the Town of Pink Hill, being Chapter 31
6 of the Private Laws of 1915, as amended by S.L. 2011-46, reads as rewritten:
7 "Sec. 3.1. In 2011 and quadrennially thereafter, the The governing body of the Town of Pink
8 Hill shall consist of a Mayor shall be elected for a four-year term. In 2011, and three
9 commissioners shall be elected, with the top vote getter receiving a four-year term and the two
10 persons receiving the next highest numbers of votes receiving two-year terms. In 2013 and
11 quadrennially thereafter, two commissioners shall be elected for four-year terms. In 2015 and
12 quadrennially thereafter, one commissioner shall be elected for a four-year term.elected to serve
13 staggered four-year terms."
14 SECTION 2. The Charter of the Town of Pink Hill, being Chapter 31 of the Private
15 Laws of 1915, as amended by Chapter 221 of the Private Laws of 1933 and by S.L. 2011-46, is
16 amended by adding a new section to read:
17 "Sec. 3.2. Regular municipal elections shall be held at the time of the general election in each
18 even-numbered year. The Mayor and commissioners shall be elected on a nonpartisan plurality
19 basis in accordance with G.S. 163-292. Except as otherwise provided, elections shall be held and
20 conducted in accordance with the uniform municipal election laws of Chapter 163 of the General
21 Statutes."
22 SECTION 3. Section 3 of the Charter of the Town of Pink Hill, being Chapter 31 of
23 the Private Laws of 1915, as amended by Chapter 221 of the Private Laws of 1933, is repealed.
24 SECTION 4. Chapter 760 of the 1955 Session Laws is repealed.
25 SECTION 5. No municipal elections shall be conducted in the Town of Pink Hill in
26 2027. The terms of office for the mayor and one commissioner in the Town of Pink Hill serving
27 on the effective date of this act whose terms are set to expire in 2027 shall be extended by one
28 year. The terms of office for the two commissioners in the Town of Pink Hill serving on the
29 effective date of this act whose terms are set to expire in 2029 shall be extended by one year.
30 Regular municipal elections in the Town of Pink Hill shall resume in even-numbered years
31 beginning in 2028 with the same staggering of terms as when elections were conducted in the
32 odd-numbered years.
33 SECTION 6. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to elections held
34 on or after that date.
